The paper deals with the security of cryptographic protocols and transformations, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of quantum adversaries and the study of their impact on the security of the Fiat-Shamir transformation suggests a connection to quantum information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the analysis of computational complexity and the reduction of quantum attacks, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.CC and cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses statistical analysis to prove security properties, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
